3
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:05,960
Captain.

4
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:06,930
Captain.

5
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:11,490
Captain.

6
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:12,370
Captain.

7
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:29,200
Ye Lan,

8
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:32,880
your intricate scheme of using others

9
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:35,320
is truly impressive.

10
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:37,940
Thank you for the compliment, Mr. Chiba.

11
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:39,329
You promised me before.

12
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:42,040
You promised to let me go abroad after getting rid of He Nan.

13
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:43,900
Can you fulfill your promise now?

14
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,610
Don't be in such a hurry.

15
00:02:46,480 --> 00:02:47,880
I still have many things

16
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:49,360
for you to do.

17
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:51,840
You can't

18
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:53,480
leave now.

19
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,640
You old fox.

20
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:57,560
One day,

21
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:00,530
I will definitely pay you back double.

22
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:07,160
Ziqing.

23
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:09,280
How are his injuries?

24
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,920
The captain is fine for now.

25
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:13,520
But his head

26
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:14,520
took a blow,

27
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:15,120
so

28
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:16,740
he hasn't woken up yet.

29
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:25,800
Shiqi,

30
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:28,800
what about the phone number I asked you to check?

31
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,960
I haven't found it yet.

32
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,520
That number is a virtual number.

33
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:32,920
It can't be traced at all.

34
00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:42,970
Captain.

35
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:43,650
Captain.

36
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:54,079
He Nan,

37
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:55,650
are you okay?

38
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:56,800
Ziqing.

39
00:03:57,640 --> 00:03:58,240
I'm fine.

40
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:02,040
Captain,

41
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:04,660
what exactly happened at OWO last night?

42
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:07,120
Last night,

43
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:09,610
I received a strange text message.

44
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:13,250
It said there were clues about Zixi's murder.

45
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,720
It asked me to meet at 10:00 PM

46
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:17,329
under the overpass.

47
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:19,519
And then?

48
00:04:22,079 --> 00:04:24,140
I don't remember what happened next.

49
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:37,240
In this Longguo Grand Prix,

50
00:04:37,520 --> 00:04:39,800
I, Ding Wen, will definitely win the championship.

51
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:41,360
Young Master Ding has outstanding driving skills.

52
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:43,560
The championship is definitely yours.

53
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:45,090
Ding Wen.

54
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:47,170
Are you Ding Wen?

55
00:04:47,840 --> 00:04:49,440
You are suspected of murder.

56
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:52,080
Please come with us to the police station for investigation.

57
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:52,640
Officer,

58
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:54,000
are you mistaken?

59
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:55,480
Me, committing a murder?

60
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:56,940
I am Young Master Ding Wen.

61
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:57,600
Tell him.

62
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:58,800
Yes, officer.

63
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,280
You must have arrested the wrong person.

64
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:02,210
This is our future world champion.

65
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:04,180
Save your excuses.

66
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:11,410
World champion, right?

67
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:12,210
Come with us.

68
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:12,920
I...

69
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:19,560
Do you remember your identity?

70
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:21,980
I remember.

71
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:27,440
You sold out Ding Wen.

72
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:30,000
I didn't know he was your man.

73
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:32,130
Did you think you could hide it from me?

74
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:32,800
Remember.

75
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:39,120
Who saved your mother's life?

76
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,159
Yes,

77
00:05:44,520 --> 00:05:45,200
Godfather.

78
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:00,930
Does it hurt?

79
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:05,300
How do you know?

80
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:08,440
Wherever that gentleman is,

81
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:10,120
I am there.

82
00:06:13,880 --> 00:06:15,140
You see him as a father,

83
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:18,640
but he only sees you as a pawn.

84
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:21,120
Watch your mouth.

85
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:23,520
Haven't you had enough?

86
00:06:26,280 --> 00:06:27,880
Why don't we

87
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,690
get rid of him together?

88
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:45,800
Mr. He.

89
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:48,040
I will keep my original promise.

90
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:50,170
I won't let your efforts be in vain.

91
00:06:50,440 --> 00:06:51,040
Also,

92
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:52,300
if you are willing,

93
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:54,480
I can take you in as my grandson.

94
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:55,850
Thank you, Elder Gu.

95
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:57,280
I'm used to living alone.

96
00:06:57,280 --> 00:06:58,280
I'll have to pass.

97
00:06:58,520 --> 00:06:59,040
He Nan.

98
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:02,840
Thank you for your contributions to the Gu Group.

99
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:04,240
My grandfather and I have discussed it,

100
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:05,960
and we plan to leave the Vice President position

101
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:07,020
of the group to you.

102
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:08,130
Young Master Gu.

103
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:10,440
I still prefer the life of an ordinary person.

104
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:11,560
You should leave the Vice President position

105
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:12,600
to someone else.

106
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:14,880
Luo Xin,

107
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,330
please see them out.

108
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:30,880
Let's celebrate the captain's return.

109
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:31,520
Cheers.

110
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:31,960
Cheers.

111
00:07:31,960 --> 00:07:33,020
Congratulations.

112
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:36,800
Finally back.

113
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:41,760
I need to take a call.

114
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:42,159
Okay.

115
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:42,840
Come on, let's continue.

116
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:43,570
Let's drink.

117
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:45,440
Drink up.

118
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:47,640
Drink more.

119
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:48,680
This wine is good.

120
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:49,080
Hello.

121
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:49,760
Lan.

122
00:07:49,960 --> 00:07:51,159
Drink up. It's so fun.

123
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:52,200
Handsome boy.

124
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:53,770
Long time no see.

125
00:07:54,520 --> 00:07:55,380
Did you miss me?

126
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:57,360
That depends on

127
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:59,420
what valuable clues you can provide.

128
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:02,240
You're so boring.

129
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:03,640
What's wrong?

130
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:06,520
Am I not worth thinking about?

131
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:08,500
Sister Lan,

132
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:11,240
can I buy you a drink to apologize some other time?

133
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,370
That's more like it.

134
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:14,240
Down to business.

135
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:17,160
I have news on what you asked me to look into.

136
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:20,540
Did you find out who hurt Zixi?

137
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:23,130
For something this important,

138
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:26,160
don't you want to come over and talk to me in person?

139
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,400
Then I'll come over right now.

140
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:28,840
Okay.

141
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:31,650
I also have a surprise waiting for you.

142
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:34,020
Wait for me.

143
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,400
Sorry.

144
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:39,890
We're closed for today.

145
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:45,680
Then we'll put the engine...

146
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:46,080
Baozi.

147
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:47,890
Take my luggage back first.

148
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:48,900
I have to go out.

149
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:50,400
Where are you going, Captain?

150
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:51,000
I

151
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:52,930
am going to see a friend.

152
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:53,760
A friend?

153
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:55,840
Ye Lan.

154
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:58,080
Captain,

155
00:08:58,480 --> 00:09:00,360
